\begin_layout Standard
Vortex rings have themselves been an object of intense study for decades,
 attracting theoreticians by the tractability of closed-form description,
 experimentalists by the ease of generation in laboratory settings, and
 developers of numerical methods by simplicity of initialization.
 However, most existing efforts focus on the single-fluid, incompressible
 case, with a handful of studies exploring multifluid mixing in incompressible
 geophysical flows, and some single-fluid studies exploring compressibility
 and shock interaction in the context of noise minimization during supersonic
 flight as depicted in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:pirozzoli-SVI"
plural "false"
