 At lower Reynolds numbers, viscosity acts to diffuse vorticity from the
 vortex core region, increasing the effective size of the core at a rate
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv{a}{t}\sim\sqrt{\nu/t}$
\end_inset

 and thus enlarging the entrainment bubble.
 In both cases, the ring radius 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

