 of diaphragm rupture required vortex ring generation to be initiated immediatel
y after detection of the main shock wave by a pressure transducer.
 Additionally, tight control of vortex generator rupture timing and pre-rupture
 gas state and composition was needed to ensure the occurrence of the shock
 wave‚Äìvortex interaction within the imaging window at a predefined imaging
 time.
