\begin_layout Standard
In lieu of (or as a precursor to) costly apparatus development, large eddy
 simulations offer a flexible, detailed means of investigating complex compressi
ble flows.
 To that end, a mature hydrodynamics code was used to simulate the interaction
 of a vortex ring with a stratified interface, followed by shock acceleration,
 across a range of conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section

\noun on
